      "span_text": "Consequently, induction of PAF release by the presence of the blastocyst, together with the synergistic vasoactive effects of PAF  and prostaglandins , could play an important physiological role in the blastocystinduced vascular permeability in the stroma of the rabbit uterus commencing at 6 days of preg¬ nancy and observable by Day 6-5 of pregnancy (Hoos & Hoffman, 1980) ."
